The Celebes Sea islands are claimed by Malaysia and Indonesia.
Sipadan Island, a top diving spot, is near Sabah, Malaysia.
The island was targeted by armed assailants, with 20 hostages taken.
Among them were an American couple who managed to escape.
The rebels responsible also abducted 27 Filipinos.
South Africans and tourists from various countries were among the hostages.
Malaysian and Philippine authorities are collaborating to locate the kidnappers.
Security forces are actively pursuing the armed pirates, who are heavily armed.
Efforts are underway to ensure the safe release of the hostages, including foreign nationals.
